\ ANS THROW / CATCH.

: bad   42 throw ;
: clean   7 . ;

\ Catching a thrown exception: the inner word's pre-throw stack is
\ rolled back; the throw code lands on the data stack.
' bad catch .

\ Clean (no-throw) execution: catch pushes 0.
' clean catch .

\ THROW with code 0 is a no-op (drops the 0 silently).
0 throw

\ Sentinel that should still print, proving the engine is alive.
99 .
